ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a great seminar class. It might have high work load, but it's really helpful.
I would definitely recommend this course. It really helps with reading papers as well as provides a great deal of depth to what is going on in CBIO 602.
It's a great way to get a taste for different fields within cell biology. I would definitely recommend it.
I would definitely recommend it as a good companion to the lecture course.
Yes. The class taught us how to think about scientificworks.
Recommend.very helpful in reading literatures and understanding the science in great details. helped thinking critically.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course is the most useful course I have ever had.

I think that this course helped deepen my knowledge of my discipline by a fair amount, as it gave me a better sense of how a lot of information was determined in the first place than a lecture course will. However, it contributed to my research by a lot, as it really gave be a better perspective on the multiple approaches to reading and dissecting papers so that I may both more efficiently and more deeply do so in the future.
I understand a lot more about cell biology than I did when I started. I realized that I want to join cell biology department.
Good experience with reading papers. Meeting in a smaller/discussion session with professors helped give me a deeper understanding of the topics discussed in lecture.
Taught me how to read articles quickly and diligently.
helped thinking critically during paper reading.
